<span id="freeTextContainer10106003653415455324">I enjoyed this book (but not the sleep it cost me when I stayed up too-late reading it) -- I&apos;ve heard of Starhawk, and this makes me curious to read more of her stuff. It&apos;s good to get a dose of utopia set in SF, and the writing is compelling. Her characters are complex as are the ways she&apos;s envisioned society (and threats to it), and I appreciate the way she wrestles with questions of non-violence vs armed rebellion, though at times the plot asked me to make jumps that didn&apos;t actually flow.</span>
  <span id="freeText10106003653415455324" style="display:none">I enjoyed this book (but not the sleep it cost me when I stayed up too-late reading it) -- I've heard of Starhawk, and this makes me curious to read more of her stuff. It's good to get a dose of utopia set in SF, and the writing is compelling. Her characters are complex as are the ways she's envisioned society (and threats to it), and I appreciate the way she wrestles with questions of non-violence vs armed rebellion, though at times the plot asked me to make jumps that didn't actually flow.</span>
